title: Tecumseh: A Chronicle of the Last Great Leader of His People
creator: Ethel T. Raymond
description: LibriVox recording of Tecumseh, by Ethel T. Raymond. Tecumseh was a leader of the Shawnee and a large tribal confederacy that opposed the United States during the War of 1812. He became a folk hero remembered by many Canadians for his defense of their country. (Summary adapted from Wikipedia) This is volume 17 in the Chronicles of Canada series. M4B audiobook of complete book For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
